physical_examinations.vital_signs: Fetal heart rate between 150 and 170 bpm
physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Renal parenchyma appeared normal on ultrasound. Significant fetal ascites with elevated diaphragm and thoracic compression observed.
Inspection of the peritoneo-amniotic shunt showed prolapse of intra-abdominal tissue (part of omentum).
Follow-up showed resolution of hydronephrosis and gradual decrease of bladder wall thickening.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Resolution of hydronephrosis and gradual decrease in bladder wall thickening observed.
